Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
Renal function is impaired as indicated by elevated creatinine. LDL cholesterol is mildly elevated, increasing cardiovascular risk. All other parameters, including glucose, electrolytes, liver enzymes, and proteins, are within normal limits. Recommend further evaluation of renal function and cardiovascular risk management.
